## Objective

Measure performance improvement from streaming canonicalization.

## Expected Impact

From PLAN:
- Current: 951 µs for long messages
- Target: ~300 µs (3x improvement)

## Benchmark Protocol

### 1. Baseline (Original Implementation)
```bash
export CASS_STREAMING_CANONICALIZE=0
cargo bench --bench runtime_perf -- canonicalize --save-baseline original
```

### 2. Streaming Implementation
```bash
unset CASS_STREAMING_CANONICALIZE
cargo bench --bench runtime_perf -- canonicalize --save-baseline streaming
```

### 3. Compare Results
```bash
critcmp original streaming
```

## Micro-Benchmarks to Add

```rust
fn bench_canonicalize(c: &mut Criterion) {
    let short = "Short message";
    let medium = include_str!("fixtures/medium_message.txt");  // ~1KB
    let long = include_str!("fixtures/long_message.txt");      // ~10KB

    let mut group = c.benchmark_group("canonicalize");

    group.bench_function("short", |b| {
        b.iter(|| canonicalize_for_embedding(black_box(short)))
    });

    group.bench_function("medium", |b| {
        b.iter(|| canonicalize_for_embedding(black_box(medium)))
    });

    group.bench_function("long", |b| {
        b.iter(|| canonicalize_for_embedding(black_box(long)))
    });

    group.finish();
}
```

## Allocation Measurement

Use jemalloc profiler to measure allocation reduction:

```bash
# Before
CASS_STREAMING_CANONICALIZE=0 cargo run --release -- bench-alloc canonicalize

# After
cargo run --release -- bench-alloc canonicalize
```

Expected:
- Allocations: 5 → 2 per call
- Total bytes allocated: ~60% reduction

## Impact on Indexing

Measure indexing throughput improvement:

```bash
# Create test corpus
cargo run --release -- index --benchmark --corpus test_corpus

# Compare indexing times
CASS_STREAMING_CANONICALIZE=0 cargo bench --bench runtime_perf -- index_small_batch
cargo bench --bench runtime_perf -- index_small_batch
```

## Success Criteria

- [ ] Long message: 951µs → ~300µs (3x improvement)
- [ ] Allocations reduced from 5 to 2
- [ ] Indexing throughput improves measurably
- [ ] Documentation updated with actual results

